Package dparser

Class Summary
Accelerometer This is a type of Message that accepts Accelerometer data.
BOverflow This Message tells when there is a buffer overflow during a datalogger write session.
CANMessage This is a message from CAN.
CANOverflow This type of message tells when there is an overflow of info coming from CAN.
CTMessage This is a CAN Transmit message.
DismountMessage This type of Message is created when the parser encounters a dismount line.
DParser Parser written for the CalSol datalogger
Message Abstract message class.
Parser Parser written for the CalSol datalogger This is the actual class that does the hard work of interpreting the datalogger signals.
SDMessage This is a message pertaining to the configs of the SD card.
SDMount This type of Message tells when the SD card was mounted.
VoltageMessage This is a statistical voltage measurement message from the datalogger.
vPerf This is a "statistical performance measurement" as documented by the Datalogger ASCII format specs.
 

Enum Summary
Parser.code This enum contains the different opCodes that are specified in the datalogger documentation.
 

Exception Summary
DecodeException Thrown when the CAN Message decoder runs into too few bytes to decode a payload properly.
